Changes to couchdb configurations required:

File : /etc/couchdb/local.ini (or similar)

// Might be irrelevant when using proxy setup with apache/nginx
enable_cors=true 

[cors]
credentials = true
origins = *


File: /etc/couchdb/default.ini (or similar)


// required in order to allow a casual user to 'see' others
[couch_httpd_auth]
public_fields=_id, name
users_db_public = true



In order to run the search functionality, one needs to install elasticsearch

1) Enable dynamic scripting. Edit elasticsearch.yml file and add the following line
script.groovy.sandbox.enable: true

2) Install the couch-river plugin from:
https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-river-couchdb

3) Restart the service and build the index from the projack settings menue